Round 1
[Patient] What foods should I eat to help manage my heart failure?
[Educator] Focus on fruits, veggies, lean proteins, and whole grains for a heart-healthy diet.

Round 2
[Patient] Can I still enjoy soul food dishes?
[Educator] You can enjoy soul food with healthier twists like baked instead of fried options.

Round 3
[Patient] Should I limit my salt intake?
[Educator] Yes, reducing salt can help manage heart failure. Try using herbs and spices for flavor.

Round 4
[Patient] Are there any specific foods I should avoid?
[Educator] Avoid processed foods, high-sodium items, and limit sweets for better heart health.

Round 5
[Patient] How important is it to stay hydrated?
[Educator] Staying hydrated is crucial for heart health. Aim for at least 8 cups of water daily.

Round 6
[Patient] Can I still have a glass of wine occasionally?
[Educator] Moderate alcohol consumption may be okay, but check with your doctor first.

Round 7
[Patient] What about caffeine?
[Educator] Limiting caffeine intake can benefit heart health. Opt for decaf or herbal teas instead.

Round 8
[Patient] Should I be mindful of portion sizes?
[Educator] Yes, controlling portion sizes can help manage heart failure. Pay attention to serving sizes.

Round 9
[Patient] Are there any specific fruits or vegetables I should focus on?
[Educator] Berries, leafy greens, and colorful veggies are great choices for heart health.

Round 10
[Patient] Can I still enjoy seafood?
[Educator] Yes, seafood like salmon and tuna are heart-healthy choices. Just watch the portion size.

Round 11
[Patient] Should I be concerned about cholesterol in my diet?
[Educator] Limiting saturated fats and cholesterol can improve heart health. Choose lean proteins and plant-based fats.

Round 12
[Patient] How can I make sure I'm getting enough fiber?
[Educator] Eating whole grains, legumes, and plenty of fruits and veggies can help you get enough fiber.

Round 13
[Patient] Are there any specific cooking methods I should use?
[Educator] Choose baking, grilling, or steaming over frying for heart-healthy cooking.

Round 14
[Patient] Can I still enjoy desserts?
[Educator] Opt for healthier dessert options like fruit salads, yogurt parfaits, or dark chocolate.

Round 15
[Patient] Thank you for the food recommendations. I feel more confident about managing my heart failure.
[Educator] You're welcome. Remember, small changes can make a big difference in your heart health.